cs.CR, cs.SY, cs.IT, cs.SE, cs.CY 

This paper deals with security and authentication mechanisms for the CAN bus, which is commonly used in automotive systems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also involves optimization algorithms for scheduling CAN frames, which falls under the category of cs.SY (Systems and Control). The use of delays and clock skews for detecting intrusions or fingerprinting ECUs on the CAN bus involves information theory, which is covered under cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also involves experiments on state-of-the-art automotive-grade controllers, which falls under the category of cs.SE (Software Engineering). Finally, the paper involves covert channels, which is covered under cs.CY (Computers and Society).
